Executive Profile
William A. Housey Jr., CFASenior Portfolio Manager, First Trust Global Funds Public Limited Company - First Trust Tactical High Yield UCITS FundAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 15 different industries.----
Background

		Mr. William A. Housey, Jr., CFA serves as Senior Vice President and Senior Portfolio Manager of First Trust Advisors L.P. Mr. Housey serves as Senior Vice President and Senior Portfolio Manager of First Trust Senior Floating Rate 2022 Target Term Fund. Mr. Housey has been Senior Portfolio Manager at First Trust Global Funds Public Limited Company - First Trust Tactical High Yield UCITS Fund and First Trust Senior Floating Rate Income Fund II since June 2010. He serves ... as Portfolio Manager at First Trust Exchange-Traded Fund IV - First Trust Tactical High Yield ETF, First Trust Exchange Traded Fund IV - First Trust Enhanced Short Maturity ETF, First Trust Variable Insurance Trust - First Trust Multi Income Allocation Portfolio, First Trust Exchange-Traded Fund IV - First Trust Strategic Income ETF, First Trust AlphaDEX Canadian Dividend ETF, First Trust Exchange-Traded Fund IV - First Trust Senior Loan Fund and First Trust Series Fund - First Trust Short Duration High Income Fund. He served as Portfolio Manager of First Trust Short Duration High Yield Bond ETF. Mr. Housey is a part of the leveraged finance team at the firm. He previously served as an Executive Director and Portfolio Manager at Van Kampen Funds, Inc. Earlier, Mr. Housey served as a Portfolio Manager of Structured Products and Senior Analyst in the Senior Loan Group at the firm. He has extensive experience in portfolio management of both leveraged and unleveraged credit products, including senior loans, high-yield bonds, credit derivatives and corporate restructurings. Mr. Houusey also has extensive retail and institutional fund raising experience. He serves on the Village of Glen Ellyn, IL Police Pension Board. Mr. Housey is a member of the CFA Institute and the CFA Society of Chicago. He holds the FINRA Series 7, Series 52 and Series 63 licenses. He holds the Chartered Financial Analyst designation. Mr. Housey received an M.B.A. in Finance, Management and Strategy from Northwestern University's Kellogg School of Business and a B.S. in Finance from Eastern Illinois University.Read Full Background




